               <msContents>
                  <summary>Pentateuch with Judeo-Italian translation and the Hebrew commentary of
                     Leone (Yehudah Aryeh) Modena</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <title xml:lang="he" key="work_3348">דגל יאודה</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc" key="work_3348">Degel Yeʾudah</title>
                     <author key="person_4948231">
                        <persName>Modena, Leone, 1571-1648</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="he">יהודה אריה מודנה</persName>
                     </author>
                     <textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="itk">Biblical text and commentary in
                        Hebrew, with Judeo-Italian translation for the biblical text</textLang>
                     <note><p>Only the Judeo-Italian translation has vocalisation.</p></note>
                     <note><p>A pen-drawn map of the Land of Israel on <locus>f. 506</locus>, which
                           is much larger than a regular folio and has been folded to fit within the
                           book, and which is accompanied by a note by <persName>Menaḥem of Vignola
                                 <foreign xml:lang="he">מנחם מרם(?) מויניולה</foreign></persName>,
                           dated <date calendar="Gregorian">1585/6</date>.</p></note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <support>paper</support>
                        <extent n="645">ff. 645 <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>298</height>
                              <width>222</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <note>ff. 387, 514 are blank.</note></extent>
                        <condition>The first leaves are slightly stained.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <summary>Italian square and semi-cursive scripts</summary>
                     <handNote>Copied by two scribes; the first, <persName ref="iph_pmr_m3c">Isaac
                           b. Elisha of <placeName key="place_97">Ruosina</placeName> (?) <foreign
                              xml:lang="he">יצחק בן אלישע מרושינה</foreign></persName>, copied
                        Genesis to Leviticus (colophon on <locus>f. 386v</locus>); the second,
                           <persName ref="fnh_pmr_m3c">Ephraim b. Yoḥanan of <placeName
                              key="place_98">Anagni</placeName> (?) <foreign xml:lang="he">אפרים בן
                              יוחנן מאנאניי</foreign></persName>, copied Numbers and Deuteronomy
                        (colophon on <locus>f. 645r</locus>).</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <p>Apart from the map on <locus>f. 506</locus>, there are two detailed
                        pen-drawn diagrams on <locus>ff. 394r and 395r</locus>, showing the Camp of
                        the Israelites and the priestly breastplate respectively.</p>
                     <p>Simple penwork frames around the initial words of Numbers and Deuteronomy
                           (<locus>ff. 388, 515</locus>). </p>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <p>Vellum over paper boards. The title (דגל יאודה) has been written in
                        Italo-Sephardic square script with brown ink on the spine, above a
                        description of the contents (פירוש על התורה וגם העתקה איטליאנו) which has
                        been written in Italo-Sephardic semi-cursive script. At the bottom of the
                        spine, a black label bearing the current shelfmark.</p>
                  </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
               <history>
                  <origin><origPlace>[Italy]</origPlace><origDate calendar="Gregorian" when="1590"
                        >1590</origDate></origin>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>Censorship certificates by <persName role="cns" ref="wvk_pmr_m3c">Camillo
                           Jaghel</persName> in <date calendar="Gregorian">1613</date>, and by
                           <persName role="cns" ref="rwk_pmr_m3c">Renato da Modena</persName> in
                           <date calendar="Gregorian">1626</date> (<locus>f. 645v</locus>).</p>
                     <p>Sold from <persName role="fmo" ref="acj_pmr_m3c">Isaac b. Mordecai Ventura
                              <foreign xml:lang="he">יצחק בן מרדכי וינטורה</foreign></persName> to
                           <persName role="fmo" ref="yfj_pmr_m3c">Jacob <foreign xml:lang="he">יעקב
                              דילמטוט</foreign></persName> in <placeName key="place_96"
                           >Venice</placeName> in <date calendar="Greogrian">1732</date>.</p>
                  </provenance>
                  <acquisition>From a collection of 69 manuscripts, partly in the possession of A.
                     Bisliches, which was bought by the Bodleian Library in <date
                        calendar="Gregorian">1850</date>.</acquisition>
               </history>
